Get Raspberry Pi Imager at 
https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/

install raspberryPI Connect 
choose bookworm 64 bit

CHOOSE DEVICE >>> Raspberry Pi4
CHOOSE OS >>> Raspberry Pi OS (64-bit) Bookworm
CHOOSE STORAGE >>> at least 32 GB

go to Raspberry Pi Connect Beta 
https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/connect/
Register wiht your email

connect Raspberry Pi camera module 2 (port Camera)
Boot raspberry PI with OS Bookworm (you need monitor, keyboard, mouse)

Open raspberryPI connect at topright screen (In raspberry pi board desktop)
Turn On Raspberry Pi Connect 
and Sign in wiht Raspberry Pi ID 
then comeback to Raspberry Pi Connect Beta and Signin with computer

At your device click at connect via
then click Screen sharing

NOW WE can CONTROL raspberry pi 4 by computer or notebook

Next step go to terminal
git clone https://github.com/VenusIntelligence-solutions/RP4objectAndMotion.git
remove python3.11/externally-managed for install opencv-python
sudo rm /usr/lib/python3.11/EXTERNALLY-MANAGED

install opencv-python
sudo pip3 install opencv-python
sudo pip3 install mediapipe

run 
  objectDetectPIcam.py 
        or 
  motionDetection.py

by thonny program

TEST ! to detect person keyboard mouse ETC 
ENJOY!
